main event: An unidentified flying object was observed in Johnston City, Illinois, on 29 July 1966, which was concluded to be a satellite.
interesting points: The object was compared to ECHO II and was stationary for 2 minutes while moving at about 1.5 degrees per second., The sighting involved a brief observation lasting one minute with an estimated angle of elevation between 45° - 60°., The observer requested identification of the satellite they believed they saw., The report indicates that the object appeared bright with constant brightness and was moving from North to Southeast., A questionnaire was included in the report to gather more information about the sighting.
sighted object: a bright object compared to ECHO II, possibly a satellite
witness description: The observer believed it was a government-supported satellite tracker and made a detailed description of the sighting.
